debugger-source-map — Phase 0: source positions through lowering + debug metadata
==================================================================================

See also:
  clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-implementation-plan.org (Phase 0, §1.2)
  clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-spec.org (§3, §4, §7, §8.1)
  issues/open/clautolisp-debugger.issue (parent tracking issue)

Context
-------

The reader already attaches a `source-span` to every parsed object
(autolisp-reader/source/model.lisp:3 and the per-object `-span` slots).
But `reader-object->runtime-value` (autolisp-runtime/source/api.lisp:1097)
lowers those position-bearing reader objects to BARE runtime values: a
`cons-object` becomes a plain CL list, an `integer-object` becomes a bare
integer, etc. The evaluator (`autolisp-eval`, api.lisp:1793) runs on the
stripped values, so NO source position survives into evaluation today.

The whole debugger (breakpoints, stepping, snapshots) depends on resolving
an executing form to its source position. This is the critical path: it
must land first and be solid.

Scope / deliverables
--------------------

1. New system `clautolisp/autolisp-source-map`, package `clautolisp.source`:
   - `source-position` = (start . end) of (file line column); EQUAL-comparable
     and printable (spec §3.5).
   - `(position-of object) -> source-position | NIL` and
     `(lines-of file) -> simple-vector of strings` (spec §3.4).

2. Form-id lowering. Extend the reader->runtime lowering (without disturbing
   the existing fast non-debug path) so that, per top-level / defun form, it:
   - assigns dense contiguous form-ids,
   - builds `form-id -> source-position`, `form-id -> kind`
     (:before-form/:after-form/:function-entry/:function-exit),
     and `parent-form-map` vectors,
   - records an EQ side-table from runtime COMPOUND forms to form-ids
     (fresh conses are EQ-unique; atoms resolve via the per-function table).

3. `function-debug-metadata` (spec §7) attached to each `autolisp-usubr`
   (new slot, or weak hash keyed by the usubr object): source-position,
   form-id->position, form-id->kind, poll-point-count, bound-names (formals +
   /-locals in binding order), parent-form-map, source-text.

4. `clautolisp.debug` skeleton: `*protocol-version*`, `thread-debug-info`
   (debug-flag, breakpoint-table, 1024-bit summary bits, inbound/outbound
   queues, current-pp, status; spec §8.1) and `*thread-debug-info-table*`.

Acceptance
----------

- `(clautolisp.source:position-of form)` returns the correct (file line col)
  for a form captured mid-evaluation.
- `function-debug-metadata` round-trips for a representative `defun` (nested
  if/while/foreach, /-locals).
- FiveAM tests in a new `.../tests` system; `*version*` bumped.
